make `entomologist-data` not a branch

Currently we store the ent db in `.git/refs/heads/entomologist-data`,
which means to git it's a regular branch, it shows up in `git branch -a`,
`git log --branches`, etc. This is rarely useful.

Move the db to `.git/refs/entomologist-data`, it still works the same
way but isn't treated by git as a normal branch.

The transition will be pretty seamless from ent's perspective, but a
bit of a pain in the ass to implement:
- `ent sync` with all remotes.
- Rename the local ref from `refs/heads/entomologist-data` to `refs/entomologist-data`.
- Push the new ref name to all remotes, while removing the old ref from the remotes.
